When generating IDEAS subkeys, why is the key shifted by 25 bits every
(128/16) = 8 subkeys. I can see that 25 being relatively prime to the
keysize makes sense, as does making the shift close to 1.5 times the
subkey-size. But wouldn't, say, 23 be just as effective?

Cheers,

